 \plain\f4\fs24 
\par\pard
{\*\bkmkstart _topicpageref_START}{\*\bkmkend _topicpageref_START}\par \pard\plain \s2\keepn\tx1200\b\f6\fs32 1.8.\tab Starting off
\par\keepn
{\v{\xe {settings}}}{\v{\xe {starting off}}}{\v{\xe {barcode}}}{\v{\xe {returns}}}{\v{\xe {wastes}}}{\v{\xe {own use}}}{\v{\xe {video member}}}{\v{\xe {rental}}}{\v{\xe {Temp A}}}{\v{\xe {Temp B}}}{\v{\xe {departments}}}{\v{\xe {supplier}}}{\v{\xe {cigarettes}}}{\v{\xe {confectionery}}}{\v{\xe {product}}}{\v{\xe {temporary}}}{\v{\xe {defaults}}}{\v{\xe {stocktaking}}}{\v{\xe {ordering}}}{\v{\xe {How do I get started?}}}\par \plain \keepn\f0\fs20 
\deflang2057\pard\plain\f4\fs24 Initially, a blank database will be installed. Log in and use the number '10000370000' as a password.
\par First enter the required entries in the '\plain\f4\fs24\cf2\ul Settings\plain\f4\fs24 ' screen. Then set up the operators of the system. It would be better to give users higher numbers and incorporate these into bar-coded passes. When this has been done, the initial operator can be downgraded to trainee, but make sure that at least one operator has an authority of zero.
\par The menu selection '\plain\f4\fs24\cf2\ul File|Print bar codes\plain\f4\fs24 ' will print out a set of six bar codes that can be attached to the operator side of the monitor to use for returns, wastes, own use, video member, charged and received on account.
\par Next, set up the departments to your liking. The existing departments can be deleted or modified provided that no sales have been entered. Retain the Rental department for rentals, and the Temp A and Temp B departments. Another recognized department is Agency. This was used for the receipt of PayPoint monies, but might be used for any money received that does not form part of the trade's takings. Aim for between ten and twenty departments in total. 
\par Finally, the key supplier details should be added to the supplier database. If for any reason it is necessary to start again, just use the menu command File\plain\f4\fs24\cf2\ul  | \plain\f4\fs24 Database | \plain\f4\fs24\cf2\ul Replace with empty database\plain\f4\fs24 '. \plain\f4\fs24\ul 
\par \plain\f4\fs24 The system can then be used, but it may be wise to add the most commonly sold products (such as cigarettes and confectionery in a convenience store) first using the \plain\f4\fs24\cf2\ul Stock |Starting stock\plain\f4\fs24  screen. 
\par For each new product encountered, a description and price have to be entered immediately to complete a sale. Additional details can be added if there is time. If a department is selected and a price entered, and the stock entry left blank, a '\plain\f4\fs24\cf2\ul New stock dialog\plain\f4\fs24 ' will be shown. 
\par However, if the department is left blank, the product is considered a temporary product. Later, using the \plain\f4\fs24\cf2\ul Stock |Starting stock\plain\f4\fs24  menu item, the department and stock details are added. These details should include default supplier and default case size. These defaults will be used later to generate the first orders.
\par After a few days, new products will be rarer. At this stage, all of the stock details can be added at the point of sale if desired, and if time allows. At this stage, stock taking should be started as a routine activity. Use the menu item \plain\f4\fs24\cf2\ul Stock |Stock take |All\plain\f4\fs24 . Later, it is preferable to use the alternative, \plain\f4\fs24\cf2\ul Stock |Stock take |All < 10\plain\f4\fs24  menu selection, as this avoids counting large numbers of items, which tends to introduce more errors than it eliminates.
\par After about three weeks, the ordering system can be brought into play.\plain\f9\fs20 \
 \
 \
 \plain\f4\fs24 
\par\pard
{\*\bkmkstart _topicpageref_settings}{\*\bkmkend _topicpageref_settings}\par \pard\plain \s2\keepn\tx1200\b\f6\fs32 1.9.\tab Settings
\par\keepn
{\v{\xe {logo}}}{\v{\xe {receipt printer}}}{\v{\xe {shelf label}}}{\v{\xe {messages}}}{\v{\xe {company}}}{\v{\xe {cheque}}}{\v{\xe {password}}}{\v{\xe {How do I customise the program for my shop?}}}{\v{\xe {printer}}}{\v{\xe {Star}}}{\v{\xe {Com 1}}}{\v{\xe {Com 2}}}{\v{\xe {Epson}}}{\v{\xe {cash drawer}}}{\v{\xe {jotter}}}{\v{\xe {guillotine}}}{\v{\xe {ProffittCenter}}}{\v{\xe {Notepad}}}{\v{\xe {How do I set it up for my company?}}}{\v{\xe {tax regime}}}{\v{\xe {Cash Limit}}}\par \plain \keepn\f0\fs20 
\deflang2057\pard\plain\f4\fs24 The Settings screen is reached by activating the menu entry \plain\f4\fs24\cf2\ul File |Settings\plain\f4\fs24  and requires that the operator has owner or manager privileges. This screen is also displayed at start-up if no database is found. It will normally be the first screen encountered after installing the program. If you have not installed MySQL via XAMPP, freely available from the "Apache Friends" website, then do this first. 
\par The Settings screen is divided into three separate tabs: server, hardware, and shop. 
\par 
\par The \plain\f4\fs24\b\i Server\plain\f4\fs24  tab holds all the required settings for connection to a database (MySQL). First there is the server name, the database name, the MySQL user name and password. The default for these are localhost (for a server running on the same computer), till, root and blank. These need to match your own setup of MySQL. For an online database, we have (for example) www.proffittcenter.org, proff2_till, proff2_test, and the password, which needs to be entered twice. 
\par The backup gmail address and Gmail password are for the automatic backing up of the database. Fill in your own gmail email address (including @gmail.com) and the gmail account password, and every time the program is closed on the machine with the server running, an email will be sent to your Google email account with an attached sql file. This can subsequently be run to reconstruct the database if something should go wrong. If you do not have a gmail account they are free from google.com and currently hold 7.5 GB of data. The program will work without this information, but for safety, always back up you data.
\par The gmail address can be your normal address, or one specifically created to hold these emails. If it is your normal address, then set up a filter to move these emails directly to a separate backup folder, skipping the inbox. This will ensure that they are archived and thus save some space, as well as keeping your inbox clear.
\par If you do not provide an email address it is essential to make alternative provision for backing up the database on a regular basis.
\par \plain\f4\fs24\b It is always necessary to click the 'Test connection' button before the main 'OK' button is enabled. 
\par \plain\f4\fs24 If an empty database engine is found, additional buttons will be enabled on the Server page to install the database, and then install tables, and these must be clicked in turn, before proceeding to the main OK button.
\par 
\par The \plain\f4\fs24\b\i Hardware\plain\f4\fs24  tab hold values for a specific hardware setup. Select an available port and then click the 'Test' button to see if the connection works. The code table and select font drop down box can be set as required. Here, in the UK, the UK setting, and the Page 19 (PC858 EURO) setting proved useful. Click 'Touch screen' if you want to use that facility. The 'Invoice printer' is for the use of an attached Windows printer instead of a receipt printer. (Not reccomended)
\par 
\par The \plain\f4\fs24\b\i Shop\plain\f4\fs24  tab hold values specific to a particular shop, such as shop name and address. Note the pound and penny symbols: insert your own for local currency. Select the character set Cp850 for a start. 
\par The tax regime for the UK, the choice is between unregistered (for VAT), registered and wholesale registered. The difference is that for wholesale, selling prices are quoted excluding VAT, and the VAT is added to the total. For retail, VAT is included in each price.
\par Then, there is a check box 'Receipt always' and 'Print receipt if greater than:'. Check this if you want a receipt to be issued for all transactions, or increase the value from zero if you want printed receipts for larger transactions only. You can always print receipts on demand by  pressing the 'Print Screen' key.
\par Set 'Autoclear in minutes' refers to the locking of the sales screen if left for an extended period. Set the value to zero if you do not want this feature.
\par The 'Float value' allows for a fixed float to be set. Leave this at zero and you will be asked to enter the float for the shift.
\par Till ID should be zero for the back office, and any low number for sales stations.
\par Unchecking the Newproduct? box will disable the creation of new product in the sales screen.
\par The checkbox labeled Close computer after saving will do what it says. When the database has grown, somewhat, the time taken to save the backup file can be tiresome, particularly in a late closing shop. Ticking this can allow you to leave the shop minutes earlier. Make sure other programs are closed down first.
\par 
\par Remember, if changes are made on any page, it is necessary to click the OK button which will save the changed values. The program will then shut down and needs to be re-started.
\par To set up with an online database, the following may be helpful.
\par I use Lunar hosts as my provider, using CPanel.
\par In CPanel click on MySQL databases. Then click Create Ne Database and fil in database name.
\par 
\par Then create a user:
\par 
\par Then add user to the database you created:
\par 
\par When you click on Add, you get a chance to grant privaleges for this user's account:
\par 
\par Having made a note of all the relavent valuse, go to File>Settings on the Server tab:
\par 
\par Then the normal process will create the database and empty tables.\plain\f9\fs20 \
 \
