{\*\bkmkstart _topicpageref_customer}{\*\bkmkend _topicpageref_customer}\par \pard\plain \s2\keepn\tx1200\b\f6\fs32 19.1.\tab New customer
\par\keepn
{\v{\xe {customer}}}{\v{\xe {new}}}{\v{\xe {video}}}{\v{\xe {member}}}{\v{\xe {default}}}{\v{\xe {telephone}}}\par \plain \keepn\f0\fs20 
\deflang2057\pard\plain\f4\fs24 Customer records are stored for one of three purposes. The first is to operate a video club and the second is to allow for credit and the third to keep track of customers when service or returns are a required part of the business. 
\par New customers can be enrolled with the Customers menu selection \plain\f8\fs24\cf0 and then clicking 'New'. \plain\f4\fs24 Customer numbers by default start at 1000380001, upwards. \plain\f8\fs24\cf0 The customer number is filled in automatically. 
\par The details of existing customers can be viewed by selecting and then clicking 'Details'.
\par 
\par \plain\f4\fs24 This will be used later to allow membership cards to be scanned into the sales screen. The fields can be stepped through using the Tab key. Names, street names etc. are capitalised on exit. There is provision for two telephone numbers, and \plain\f8\fs24\cf0 provision for a second card holder with a different name\plain\f4\fs24 .
\par The print bar code button allows a membership card to be printed. The print is onto the default printer, using a small note size piece of paper. After being signed, this can be folded in half, trimmed with scissors, and then sealed with a credit card size laminating machine. The use of heat sealing to laminate the card stops a thermal receipt printer being used, so the cards are printed on the default printer.\plain\f8\fs24\cf0 
\par The details to be filled in are self explanatory. For video club members there is provision for a second card holder with a different name. All entries will be capitalised, so stick to lower case for maximum convenience. \plain\f9\fs20\cf0 \
 \
 \
 \plain\f8\fs24\cf0 
\par\pard
{\*\bkmkstart _topicpageref_customers}{\*\bkmkend _topicpageref_customers}\par \pard\plain \s2\keepn\tx1200\b\f6\fs32 19.2.\tab Customers
\par\keepn
{\v{\xe {member}}}{\v{\xe {name}}}{\v{\xe {street}}}{\v{\xe {postcode}}}{\v{\xe {customers}}}\par \plain \keepn\f0\fs20 
\deflang2057\pard\plain\f4\fs24 Select the menu item Customers and then choose between By name, or By  number. Customers will be listed in the specified order in tabular form. Use the scroll bar to move beyond the visible list. Select any line and then click the 'Details' button to see customer details. With this selected, the full details of the customer with the option to print a new membership card for an account is shown. Details can be altered and then saved by clicking the OK button. One option that can be changed is the stop tick box. Ticking this will stop further goods being taken by customers with unpaid bills. 
\par The same form, sorted by name is shown when the customer select number, \plain\f5\fs24\cf0 1000380000\plain\f4\fs24  is entered at the sales screen, or a 'charge' or 'received on account' is requested without first selecting a customer. A member can be selected by clicking on a name with the mouse and then clicking the OK button; or scanning an account button. 
\par Bear in mind that the Data Protection Act in the UK, and similar regulations elsewhere, may mean that personal data cannot be shared with other customers at the counter without the consent of the person involved.
\par The same form is used to select a customer: just scroll through and click on a customer and then press the Enter key. You can also scan or type in a Customer code followed by Tab or Enter.
\par To charge a sale to a customer, simply scan the customer barcode at some time during the sale, or using 'Customers|Customers by name', select the customer and then press the Enter key. Finally Charge the customer account by scanning the 'Charge' barcode or typing 1000034 followed by Tab or Enter.
\par To refund a customer for returned goods, scan as normal and then press the - (minus) key followed by the Tab or Enter key. The goods will be returned to stock.  To return all the items 'sold' so far, press the minus key and then holding down the shift key, press Enter. Finally charge this to the previously selected customer by scanning the 'Charge' barcode.
\par If at any time the Charge barcode is scanned without selecting a customer, the 'Customers by name' screen appears and you can select a customer at that stage with a mouse followed by the Enter key. With the 'Customers by name' screen visible, it is still possible to scan a customer barcode for selection.
\par To make a payment off an account, with a customer selected, scan the 'Received' barcode or type 1000035 followed by Tab or Enter. The account balance will be shown as a total, and any amount paid in may be typed in. If this is just an enquiry, enter a zero followed by enter. It is possible to pay money into an account, when no money is owed. Simply press the shift key when pressing the Enter key. To return money paid in this way without purchasing goods, do an enquiry as above, but then type zero, and then hold the shift key down as you press enter.
\par The screen can also be manipulated entirely by keyboard characters: use the up and down arrows to move the selection up and down, or the page up and page down to jump through the customer names. Use the + sign to create a new customer and Control-I key to see customer details of a selected customer. If a customer barcode is scanned, this is returned as a customer number.\plain\f9\fs20 \
 \
 \
 \plain\f4\fs24 
\par\pard
{\*\bkmkstart _topicpageref_Accounts}{\*\bkmkend _topicpageref_Accounts}\par \pard\plain \s2\keepn\tx1200\b\f6\fs32 19.3.\tab Accounts
\par\keepn
\par \plain \keepn\f0\fs20 
\deflang2057\pard\plain\f4\fs24 For products that are charged, sell as normal and then scan the charged bar code or type \plain\f8\fs24\cf0 1000034\plain\f4\fs24  followed by the enter key or use the menu option 'Payment|Charge'. If a customer has not been defined, the \plain\f4\fs24\cf2\ul Customers screen\plain\f4\fs24  is displayed. Select the name of the desired customer with the mouse and then press the OK button. A new customer entry can be created clicking the \plain\f4\fs24\cf2\ul New customer\plain\f4\fs24  button. 
\par Subsequently, accounts must be paid for if you are to remain in business. On an empty sales screen, scan the received on account bar code, type \plain\f8\fs24\cf0 1000035 or use the menu option 'Payment|Received on account'. The \plain\f8\fs24\cf2\ul Customers\plain\f8\fs24\cf0  screen will be displayed to select the correct customer. Alternatively, a customer account card with a customer number as a barcode can be scanned, to obviate the need to select a customer. Then the outstanding balance will be shown and any amount may be tendered to reduce this. Any balance will be carried forward. If zero is entered as a tender, the sales screen is cleared, allowing for a quick account balance check.
\par The bar codes for charged and received on account can be printed out using the \plain\f8\fs24\cf2\ul print bar codes\plain\f8\fs24\cf0  option.
\par Two keyboard shortcuts are provided for these functions: < (cash in, received on account) for received on account and > (goods out, charged) for charged.
\par \plain\f5\fs20\cf0 \
 \
 \
 \plain\f3\fs20\cf0 
\par\pard
{\*\bkmkstart _topicpageref_balance}{\*\bkmkend _topicpageref_balance}\par \pard\plain \s2\keepn\tx1200\b\f6\fs32 19.4.\tab Balance
\par\keepn
\par \plain \keepn\f0\fs20 
\deflang2057\pard\plain\f3\fs24\cf0 Selecting 'Customers|Balane' on the menu brings up the 'Customer by name' screen which is used to select a customer. Select one by clicking and then press the OK button to display the 'Balance' screen.
\par This shows a list of outstanding items purchased, and money received on account, together with the sale ID. At the bottom is the total charged and the total received since the account was opened, and the balance outstanding. Clear with the Escape key or clicking the Close button marked with a small x.\plain\f5\fs20\cf0 \
 \
 \
 \plain\f3\fs24\cf0 
\par\pard
{\*\bkmkstart _topicpageref_balances}{\*\bkmkend _topicpageref_balances}\par \pard\plain \s2\keepn\tx1200\b\f6\fs32 19.5.\tab Balances
\par\keepn
\par \plain \keepn\f0\fs20 
\deflang2057\pard\plain\f3\fs24\cf0 This screen shows a list of all customers and their total charged, received and their net balance. Selecting a customer and clicking details will display the 'Balance' screen for that customer.\plain\f5\fs20\cf0 \
 \
